This article is a Presidential Proclamation by Barack Obama declaring July 27, 2010, as National Korean War Veterans Armistice Day. The proclamation commemorates the signing of the Military Armistice Agreement at Panmunjom and honors the servicemembers who fought and died in the Korean War. It acknowledges the 60th anniversary of the war and highlights the enduring friendship between the United States and the Republic of Korea. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities that honor Korean War veterans.